{% block content %}

  <article>

    <header class="post-header">
      <div class="post-header-inner">
        <a href="/services/" class="post-breadcrumb">&larr; All Services</a>
        <span class="blog-category">Service</span>
        <h1>SEO Services That Get Your Business Found on Google</h1>
        <div class="post-meta">
          <span>By <strong>Freeland Marketing &amp; Entertainment</strong></span>
          <span>Palm Coast, FL</span>
          <span>Serving Businesses Nationwide</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="post-featured-img">
      <picture>
        <img src="/blog/images/service-seo-florida.jpg" alt="SEO services for businesses — reviewing search rankings and organic traffic" width="860" height="480" />
      </picture>
    </div>

    <div class="post-body">

      <p style="font-size:1.15rem;line-height:1.7;">Right now, someone is searching Google for exactly what your business sells. "Best contractor near me." "Dentist open Saturday." "Marketing agency for restaurants." If your business does not show up on the first page, that customer is going to your competitor. Every single time.</p>

      <p>Most businesses have websites that are invisible on Google. They were built, launched, and forgotten — with no SEO strategy, no monitoring, and no one watching whether they actually rank. Some have been hurt by bad past SEO work — keyword stuffing, spam links, or outdated techniques that now get penalized.</p>

      <p><strong>We fix what is broken, set up professional monitoring, and keep your site performing month after month.</strong></p>

      <div class="stat-grid">
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-number">75%</div>
          <div class="stat-label">of users never scroll past page 1 of Google</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-number">46%</div>
          <div class="stat-label">of all Google searches have local intent</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-number">28%</div>
          <div class="stat-label">of local searches result in a purchase within 24 hours</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-number">0%</div>
          <div class="stat-label">of SEO traffic costs you per click (unlike ads)</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>How It Works: Two Phases</h2>

      <div class="phase-grid">

        <div class="phase-card">
          <span class="phase-label">Phase 1 — Foundation</span>
          <h3>Fix What's Broken</h3>
          <p>A complete audit and remediation of your website's SEO. We find every issue and fix it.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Complete website SEO audit (every page reviewed)</li>
            <li>Security scan for malware, spam, or injected content</li>
            <li>Fix all meta titles and descriptions</li>
            <li>Fix heading structure across every page</li>
            <li>Set up or fix XML sitemap and robots.txt</li>
            <li>Add schema markup (tells Google what your business is)</li>
            <li>Set up Open Graph tags for social sharing</li>
            <li>Set up Google Search Console and submit sitemap</li>
            <li>Set up Google Analytics (if not already in place)</li>
            <li>Full report of everything found and fixed</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="phase-note">One-time engagement. Typically completed in 1-2 weeks. Custom quote based on site size and issue severity.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="phase-card">
          <span class="phase-label">Phase 2 — Ongoing Monitoring</span>
          <h3>Keep It Working</h3>
          <p>Automated monitoring and monthly optimization so your rankings keep improving.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Keyword rank tracking (50-100 keywords, weekly)</li>
            <li>Automated weekly site health crawls</li>
            <li>Backlink monitoring (gain/loss alerts)</li>
            <li>24/7 uptime monitoring (instant alerts)</li>
            <li>Monthly branded SEO report delivered to your inbox</li>
            <li>Fix new technical issues as they are detected</li>
            <li>Google Search Console monitoring</li>
            <li>Quarterly strategy review call</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="phase-note">Month-to-month after initial commitment. Custom quote based on your goals and competitive landscape.</div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <p style="text-align:center;color:#888;font-size:0.9rem;">Every business is different. We quote pricing after reviewing your site, competition, and goals — so you get a plan that fits, not a one-size-fits-all package.</p>

      <h2>What You Don't Have to Do</h2>

      <p>Nothing. The monitoring runs automatically. We review the data, fix issues as they come up, and send you a clear report every month showing exactly what changed and why. You focus on running your business — we handle the SEO.</p>

      <h2>Industries We Serve</h2>

      <div class="industry-grid">
        <div class="industry-item">
          <strong>Restaurants &amp; Hospitality</strong>
          <span>Google Business Profile, local Map Pack, review strategy</span>
        </div>
        <div class="industry-item">
